<br>
I cannot say much about american laws but the situation expressed by Maddie does not call for an arrest in my opinion.<br>
<br>
Two times a day is passed the casual smoker status however but considering the times he does it and that a buzz does not last more than 2 hours ( will not hamper his morning productivity) I don't think it really affects society to any point that any mesures should be taken.<br>
<br>
His children getting a bad example, and him losing moral high ground is wrong however. He can no longer use parents generic line #XYZ &quot;Don't do this, it's wrong&quot; since he himself is doing drugs, however, he can use the &quot;I've been there before and know what it's like&quot;.  This man is setting a bad example for his kids only if he tries to deny that what he is doing is wrong. He could however also use this and educate his kids about drugs and not keep them ignorent.<br>
<br>
This man is not teaching his kids to use any other drugs, he is not supporting Coke, Hero, Crack .... He is using pot and can still properly educate his children to stay away from the harder more noxious drugs.<br>
<br>
A joint is no worse than a cigarette, it is no more a gateway drug than nicotine.<br>
<br>
