<br>
Smoking a joint twice a day is bad for his kids for a number reasons in my opinion.<br>
 <br>
First unlike a cigarette - it is illegal. It doesn't really matter if you agree with it or not. He is teaching his children by example that you don't need to follow the law. It is a bad lesson to teach your kids. Laws should not be followed blindly - the Civil Rights Movement is a great example of when laws should be broken. But smoking pot isn't a civil rights struggle now is it? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  What if our fictious parent decided drunk driving was acceptable? That is not that far a stretch from getting baked twice a day. <br>
<br>
In addition he is teaching them that drug use is acceptable. While he may not be teaching them to use coke, heroin or other truly terrible drugs he is certainly teaching them to use pot. If it stopped right there ask yourself if that &quot;Is that OK?&quot; - personally I don't think so. While not heroin or coke - pot certainly has is downfalls. The only advantage to smoking pot is it's intoxicating effect (and some medical benefits - but we are not talking about a cataract patient <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). I chose to not expose my kids to drugs at all and alcohol only in moderation. My kids have never seen me drunk and I stopped using drugs when I became a father. I want my kids to see a clear-headed adult making responsible decisions. That is the example I want to set for my kids. His kids will certainly smoke pot because that is &quot;normal&quot; - when they rebel in their teen years what shall they do? <br>
<br>
Also where is he getting the pot? Buying it? Growing it? If he is buying it wouldn't his kids be better served with the money being saved? Invested for college? Anything but buying drugs. If he is growing - then he is probably looking at jail time if he is caught. By growing he would be taking a HUGE risk. And I didn't know anyone who grew and didn't sell. I will assume he is buying and not growing. When I smoked getting baked twice a day would cost between $10-$15 bucks a day. Let's assume the prices are pretty close (I have no idea if they are <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) that's between $300 and $450 per month. That's a NICE brand new car if he chose to spend the money. It could be a college fund for his kids. Using the money for anything but drugs helps his family more than drug use - anything.<br>
<br>
Should he be arrested? Nope - but again I would suggest he would be better off quitting. So would his family.<br>
<br>
My opinion is based on the events of my life - your mileage will vary. I am trying to not sound too preachy... afterall I did smoke everyday for years <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center>
